remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-118">O padrão para o `value` usa o parâmetro de cadeia de caracteres vazia ("").</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-118">The default for the `value` parameter uses the empty string ("").</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-119">O `value` parâmetro para um <xref:System.Net.Cookie> não deve ser um `null` referência (Nothing no Visual Basic).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-119">The `value` parameter for a <xref:System.Net.Cookie> must not be a `null` reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-120">O ponto e vírgula (";") e vírgula (",") caracteres são reservados e não podem ser passados a `value` parâmetro, a menos que a cadeia de caracteres transmitida a `value` parâmetro é colocado entre aspas duplas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-120">The semicolon (";") and comma (",") characters are reserved and cannot be passed in the `value` parameter unless the string passed in the `value` parameter is enclosed in double quotes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-121">Portanto o seguinte construtor de exemplo teria êxito, mas quando você tenta adicionar isso <xref:System.Net.Cookie> para um <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instância com o <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> ou <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> métodos, a operação falhar e lançar uma exceção:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-121">So the following example constructor would succeed, but when you try to add this <xref:System.Net.Cookie> to a <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instance with the <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> or <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> methods, the operation will fail and throw an exception:</span></span>  
  
 ```
 System.Net.Cookie cookie = new System.Net.Cookie("contoso", "123,456");
 cookie.Domain = "https://contoso.com";
 new CookieContainer().Add(cookie);
 ```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-122">No entanto, o seguinte construtor com os seguintes caracteres especiais escapado criará uma <xref:System.Net.Cookie> que podem ser adicionados a um <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instância:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-122">However, the following constructor with these special characters escaped will create a <xref:System.Net.Cookie> that can be added to a <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instance:</span></span>  
 
 ```
 System.Net.Cookie cookie = new System.Net.Cookie("contoso", "\"123,456\"");
 cookie.Domain = "https://contoso.com";
 new CookieContainer().Add(cookie);
 ```
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-123">O caractere de vírgula é usado como um delimitador entre cookies separados na mesma linha.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-123">The comma character is used as a delimiter between separate cookies on the same line.</span></span>

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-141">O padrão para o `path` usa o parâmetro de cadeia de caracteres vazia ("").</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-141">The default for the `path` parameter uses the empty string ("").</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-142">O `value` parâmetro para um <xref:System.Net.Cookie> não deve ser um `null` referência (Nothing no Visual Basic).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-142">The `value` parameter for a <xref:System.Net.Cookie> must not be a `null` reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-143">O ponto e vírgula (";") e vírgula (",") caracteres são reservados e não podem ser passados a `value` parâmetro, a menos que a cadeia de caracteres transmitida a `value` parâmetro é colocado entre aspas duplas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-143">The semicolon (";") and comma (",") characters are reserved and cannot be passed in the `value` parameter unless the string passed in the `value` parameter is enclosed in double quotes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f0f20-144">Portanto o seguinte construtor de exemplo teria êxito, mas quando você tenta adicionar isso <xref:System.Net.Cookie> para um <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instância com o <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> ou <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> métodos, a operação falhar e lançar uma exceção:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f0f20-144">So the following example constructor would succeed, but when you try to add this <xref:System.Net.Cookie> to a <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instance with the <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> or <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> methods, the operation will fail and throw an exception:</span></span>  
  
 ```
